Endocavitary and intraoperative ultrasonography and radioimmunolocalization of solid neoplasms supporting staging and therapeutic strategy in oncological surgery. Endocavitary and intraoperative ultrasound, as well as malignancies radioimmunolocalization, support surgery in the correct therapeutical planning, offering details about the real extension of neoplastic disease, necessary parameter, which sometimes is unexpectedly revisited, compared with preoperative informations. The invasiveness of both instrumental procedures is balanced by evident advantages, regarding global accuracy, either sensitivity or specificity.